<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:33.595 --> 01:36.350
‐ Okay, so,
the water damage

01:36.350 --> 01:38.731
made a lot of this
indecipherable,

01:38.731 --> 01:43.197
but I think that
I finally figured out...

01:43.197 --> 01:46.245
what this could possibly be.

01:46.245 --> 01:48.374
And I think that we are looking
at the very first draft

01:48.374 --> 01:49.961
of The Ladder.

01:49.961 --> 01:51.631
‐
‐

01:51.631 --> 01:54.971
‐

01:54.971 --> 01:57.643
‐ And I believe
that there's a second author.

01:57.643 --> 01:59.438
‐ What?
‐ Um, so right here,

01:59.438 --> 02:03.697
The Light is not described
as a benevolent force,

02:03.697 --> 02:08.080
but, "A fire that cleanses
and burns."

02:09.166 --> 02:12.088
‐ The woman...

02:12.088 --> 02:14.468
from the video, Lilith.

02:14.468 --> 02:16.305
‐ Well, possibly.
Look at this.

02:16.305 --> 02:17.934
I mean, Sarah, even
the handwriting is different.

02:17.934 --> 02:21.023
‐ No, but if she helped
him write this...

02:21.023 --> 02:22.860
It doesn't work
with someone else.

02:22.860 --> 02:25.574
‐ What?
‐ The story.

02:25.574 --> 02:27.244
Look, I know you think
it's ridiculous

02:27.244 --> 02:29.456
that Dr. Steven Meyer
climbed a ladder of fire

02:29.456 --> 02:31.126
and received the rungs, but‐‐

02:31.126 --> 02:32.755
‐ It's no more ridiculous
than parting the Red Sea

02:32.755 --> 02:34.634
or turning water into wine.

02:34.634 --> 02:36.680
They're the foundational myths
of every great faith.

02:36.680 --> 02:38.725
‐ It's not supposed to
be a myth.

02:38.725 --> 02:42.900
You know, never once in my life
did I ever question truth.

02:44.319 --> 02:46.741
If there's no Light,
then what else is there?

02:50.206 --> 02:53.129
‐ There's doubt, Sarah...

02:53.129 --> 02:55.258
and fear of death.

02:55.258 --> 02:57.137
And there is

02:57.137 --> 03:00.101
this urgent...

03:00.101 --> 03:02.815
immediacy to life.

03:02.815 --> 03:04.276
Listen to me.

03:06.531 --> 03:08.409
There's a life
you haven't lived yet...

03:08.409 --> 03:11.958
with sushi and college.

03:11.958 --> 03:14.087
‐ It's too late for that.
‐ Is it?

03:26.487 --> 03:29.911
Sarah, I know this
is painful right now...

03:31.205 --> 03:34.252
But there's so much that's
miraculous on the other side.

03:37.760 --> 03:40.974
‐ This wasn't just
research for you.

03:40.974 --> 03:43.145
‐ Sorry?

03:48.072 --> 03:50.243
‐ You did this for me.

03:50.243 --> 03:53.165
‐ It's work I love.

03:53.165 --> 03:57.090
Yes. I wanted you to know
what you'd found.

03:57.090 --> 04:00.221
I'm sorry if this makes you
uncomfortable. I underst‐‐

04:15.836 --> 04:17.380
‐ How's your first
week of work?

04:17.380 --> 04:19.886
‐ It's nice to be
on this side of the desk.

04:19.886 --> 04:22.140
‐ Well, let us know
if there's anything you need.

04:22.140 --> 04:23.769
Oh, and there's someone
here in the lobby.

04:23.769 --> 04:25.939
Do you have time for a walk‐in?
‐ Sure.

04:41.805 --> 04:43.850
Hello, Mary.

04:45.771 --> 04:48.484
You don't look happy
to see me.

04:48.484 --> 04:51.991
‐ Last time I saw you,
you held my head underwater.

04:51.991 --> 04:55.874
‐ That's right.
You were angry when you left.

04:55.874 --> 04:58.295
Weren't you?
‐ What are you doing here?

04:58.295 --> 05:01.594
‐ I'm here for help.
That's your job, isn't it?

05:01.594 --> 05:03.305
You help people
with drug problems.

05:03.305 --> 05:04.559
‐ Harold‐‐

05:04.559 --> 05:06.980
‐ I take 20 painkillers a day,

05:06.980 --> 05:09.861
and still it hurts
just to get out of bed.

05:09.861 --> 05:13.284
My body is broken, Mary,

05:13.284 --> 05:15.873
and all I've got to show for it
is a couple of measly rings.

05:15.873 --> 05:17.292
‐ Listen to me‐‐
‐ Granted, they're worth

05:17.292 --> 05:19.379
50,000 each,

05:19.379 --> 05:22.678
but those rings
cost me everything.

05:22.678 --> 05:26.519
‐ And I always noticed
Small Saul looking at them...

05:26.519 --> 05:28.397
coveting them.

05:28.397 --> 05:30.276
‐ Small Saul?
‐ Yeah.

05:30.276 --> 05:33.240
I mean, if anyone took
those rings, it was him.

05:35.411 --> 05:37.040
What?

05:37.040 --> 05:39.712
‐ I didn't say
they were missing.

05:44.429 --> 05:46.141
I got you.

05:49.523 --> 05:52.947
‐ What's wrong?
‐ I'm so sorry.

05:52.947 --> 05:55.535
‐ Harold. What‐‐Hey‐‐
No, no.

05:55.535 --> 05:57.748
Hold on. Ho‐‐ho‐‐ho‐‐oh‐‐

05:57.748 --> 05:59.752
‐ It's so good to see you.

05:59.752 --> 06:01.171
‐ Oh.

06:01.171 --> 06:03.008
‐ And Forest too.
‐ Yeah.

06:03.008 --> 06:04.929
Wait, no. Hey, what the hell
are you doing here?

06:04.929 --> 06:07.685
‐ I stole his rings,
and then, um, I‐‐

06:07.685 --> 06:09.020
I sold them,
but I lost the money.

06:09.020 --> 06:10.481
‐ Wait, what‐‐what?

06:10.481 --> 06:12.193
‐ I left them
in the diaper bag.

06:12.193 --> 06:14.155
My dad took them.
‐ Sorry, what‐‐what are you‐‐

06:14.155 --> 06:15.826
‐ But I'm tracking my dad.
I'm gonna get the money back.

06:15.826 --> 06:17.161
‐ Wait, Mary, what the hell
have you done?

06:17.161 --> 06:20.877
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey.
‐ Shh.

06:20.877 --> 06:22.422
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:22.422 --> 06:24.885
I don't care
about the money, Mary.

06:27.223 --> 06:29.895
You and I are going
on a treasure hunt.

06:31.356 --> 06:33.695
Yes, we are.

06:33.695 --> 06:36.408
Yes, we are. Me and Daddy.

06:45.927 --> 06:49.476
‐ I see Peru
was transformative.

06:49.476 --> 06:51.188
‐

06:51.188 --> 06:53.651
‐ You left a gardener
and came back a handyman.

06:53.651 --> 06:56.114
‐ I'll have you know, I built
the very first dorm on campus.

06:56.114 --> 06:57.659
‐ Uh, yeah. No, I know.

06:57.659 --> 06:59.747
That's the one
that collapsed, right?

06:59.747 --> 07:02.126
‐ Lasted eight months.

07:02.126 --> 07:04.799
I just thought Summer
would enjoy a tree house.

07:04.799 --> 07:07.345
I had one growing up,
and, uh‐‐

07:07.345 --> 07:09.390
Eh, maybe she's
too old for it.

07:09.390 --> 07:12.313
I just feel bad
about missing her in her play.

07:12.313 --> 07:14.442
‐ She's gonna love it.

07:14.442 --> 07:16.279
You, uh, you want some help?

07:16.279 --> 07:18.158
‐ I think
the Guardian of the Light

07:18.158 --> 07:19.954
has more pressing matters.

07:22.501 --> 07:24.212
Uh, no.

07:24.212 --> 07:26.299
‐ What?

07:26.299 --> 07:30.182
‐ Are we really opening
a center in France?

07:30.182 --> 07:33.565
‐ Yeah. I'm leaving in a couple
days to consecrate it myself.

07:35.401 --> 07:38.198
‐ This is huge, Eddie.

07:38.198 --> 07:42.039
‐ You know, I was thinking
that I'm gonna need someone

07:42.039 --> 07:43.751
to go out there
in a few months,

07:43.751 --> 07:45.672
you know,
check on the progress.

07:45.672 --> 07:48.803
You and Gaby up for the job?

07:52.185 --> 07:55.065
Oh.

07:55.065 --> 07:58.488
You know, you should
grip further down.

07:58.488 --> 08:00.034
‐ What?
‐ On the hammer.

08:00.034 --> 08:03.207
‐ Oh.
‐ You're holding it like this.

08:03.207 --> 08:06.421
A little further down,
you get more leverage.

08:06.421 --> 08:08.091
‐
‐ See? Hear the difference?

08:08.091 --> 08:10.346
‐ Well, you have your method,
I have mine.

08:10.346 --> 08:12.350
‐ Fair enough.

08:12.350 --> 08:14.229
‐ Hey, don't tell Gaby
about France.

08:14.229 --> 08:16.859
I want it to be a surprise.
‐ You got it.

08:30.720 --> 08:33.308
Taking a break already, huh?

08:34.645 --> 08:38.068
Hank.

08:38.068 --> 08:40.447
Hey!

08:40.447 --> 08:44.455
Hey. Hey, hey. Hey.
Oh, shit. Hey. Hey.

08:44.455 --> 08:46.001
Help!
‐

08:46.001 --> 08:47.336
‐ Call someone.

08:47.336 --> 08:49.633
Hey, Hank. Hey, Hank.

08:49.633 --> 08:51.846
Hank. Hey.

08:55.770 --> 08:58.442
‐ I've never been
with a heathen before.

09:01.657 --> 09:03.661
‐
Do you feel corrupted?

09:06.416 --> 09:08.838
‐ I feel... good.

09:08.838 --> 09:11.677
‐ Mm‐hmm.

09:11.677 --> 09:15.518
‐ Mm. Do you hear something?

09:15.518 --> 09:17.856
‐ What?
‐ Mm.

09:17.856 --> 09:20.152
‐ Let me check.

09:24.285 --> 09:26.666
‐ Stop.

09:46.997 --> 09:51.089
‐ If you could call
the outpost in France...

09:51.089 --> 09:55.974
‐ Yeah, I've already let them
know we need to postpone.

09:55.974 --> 10:01.109
‐ God, I was supposed
to teach a workshop tonight.

10:01.109 --> 10:02.904
‐ All classes
have been canceled.

10:02.904 --> 10:04.365
In fact, I've cleared
your schedule

10:04.365 --> 10:05.660
for the rest
of the week, Eddie.

10:05.660 --> 10:07.664
You don't‐‐you‐‐

10:07.664 --> 10:10.169
you don't need to focus
on anything but this.

10:10.169 --> 10:12.298
Okay?

10:14.845 --> 10:17.141
‐ I should head inside.

10:17.141 --> 10:19.145
‐ Eddie.

10:19.145 --> 10:22.234
I know you have to be a rock
for the community right now,

10:22.234 --> 10:25.992
but you really don't need
to be that way with me.

10:29.917 --> 10:31.712
‐

10:33.758 --> 10:35.720
God.

10:41.565 --> 10:44.822
‐ Well, if you need anything,

10:44.822 --> 10:47.159
anytime, I'm‐‐I'm here.

10:47.159 --> 10:48.955
‐

10:48.955 --> 10:50.374
‐ Okay?

10:54.842 --> 10:55.969
What?

10:59.183 --> 11:01.814
‐ I'm just, uh‐‐

11:01.814 --> 11:04.736
just lucky to have you is all.

11:15.800 --> 11:20.017
As the owl
protects The Garden...

11:20.017 --> 11:24.860
we offer Hank these wings...

11:24.860 --> 11:27.239
to carry him home...

11:27.239 --> 11:29.661
To be his guide...

11:29.661 --> 11:32.124
‐ And to help watch‐‐

11:39.096 --> 11:46.110
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:49.325 --> 11:52.540
‐ Did I‐‐did I miss it?

11:52.540 --> 11:55.797
‐ Hank waited for you.

11:55.797 --> 11:58.594
‐ I never heard my‐‐
‐ Mm, mm, mm...

11:58.594 --> 12:02.476
You're here now.
That's all that matters here.

12:18.843 --> 12:23.184
‐ Sarah, we were about
to start the blessing.

12:23.184 --> 12:25.439
I was hoping
that you would lead it.

12:28.696 --> 12:30.407
‐ Oh.

12:30.407 --> 12:33.371
‐

12:40.678 --> 12:42.640
‐ We believe in The Light.

12:44.561 --> 12:46.397
We believe Hank Armstrong

12:46.397 --> 12:50.197
will live
his light in The Garden.

12:50.197 --> 12:52.619
We believe in The Garden,

12:52.619 --> 12:54.497
for all this was revealed
to Steven Meyer

12:54.497 --> 12:57.294
as he ascended The Ladder
and received the rungs.

12:59.966 --> 13:04.684
‐ We now invite Hank to leave
this earthly form behind,

13:04.684 --> 13:07.022
for in ending...

13:07.022 --> 13:08.609
We begin.

13:08.609 --> 13:11.990
- ‐ And in sorrow...
- We rejoice.

13:11.990 --> 13:15.413
- ‐ And in darkness...
- There is light.

13:18.128 --> 13:21.134
‐

13:35.955 --> 13:38.084
‐ Sure this is the place?

13:38.084 --> 13:40.005
‐ This is the address
she gave us.

13:40.005 --> 13:42.467
‐ I'm glad you weren't
a part of this,

13:42.467 --> 13:45.473
'cause if my lady
had kept me in the dark,

13:45.473 --> 13:48.229
played me the way
Mary played you...

13:56.412 --> 14:01.590
♪ ♪

14:07.852 --> 14:09.814
‐ Wait for starter pistol.

14:09.814 --> 14:11.902
Nina.

14:19.960 --> 14:21.922
Ohh!

14:21.922 --> 14:25.011
Ah, still undefeated, eh?

14:25.011 --> 14:28.184
Ah. Who's next?

14:28.184 --> 14:30.606
‐ Me.

14:30.606 --> 14:34.238
Last month you bought

14:34.238 --> 14:37.244
two championship rings.

14:37.244 --> 14:41.168
Now, those rings are very
valuable to my friend here.

14:41.168 --> 14:42.964
If I beat you...

14:44.383 --> 14:46.470
We get them back.

14:46.470 --> 14:49.143
‐

14:49.143 --> 14:52.525
I like you.

14:52.525 --> 14:54.821
But I am middleman.

14:54.821 --> 14:56.950
I sold the rings.

14:56.950 --> 15:00.415
But I will tell you
who I sold them to

15:00.415 --> 15:02.962
if your friend can beat me.

15:02.962 --> 15:04.841
‐ Deal.
‐ Hey, no. No deal.

15:04.841 --> 15:07.095
No deal. I need you
to remain in control.

15:07.095 --> 15:10.143
I will handle this.

15:10.143 --> 15:12.439
You're a businessman.

15:12.439 --> 15:14.569
Okay, so I'm gonna
make you a proposition.

15:14.569 --> 15:16.238
Aah!

15:18.242 --> 15:20.664
‐ See?

15:20.664 --> 15:22.627
You are weak.

15:22.627 --> 15:26.510
But your friend here
is perfect physical specimen.

15:27.762 --> 15:32.270
If he wins,
I will give you address.

15:32.270 --> 15:35.653
If I win...

15:35.653 --> 15:38.491
We shoot you in the head.

15:45.463 --> 15:46.716
Come.

15:46.716 --> 15:53.730
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:02.289 --> 16:03.876
Nina.

16:03.876 --> 16:10.848
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:12.685 --> 16:13.979
Aah!

16:13.979 --> 16:16.483
Oh!

16:16.483 --> 16:20.116
‐

16:21.828 --> 16:24.584
‐ ♪ Flowers cast
off their petals ♪

16:24.584 --> 16:27.506
♪ And the trees shed
all their leaves ♪

16:27.506 --> 16:30.345
♪ The sky began to weep
with rain ♪

16:30.345 --> 16:33.267
♪ But The Light said,
"Do not grieve." ♪

16:33.267 --> 16:38.987
♪ There's a world
beyond this world ♪

16:38.987 --> 16:44.373
♪ With warmth and love
and song ♪

16:44.373 --> 16:50.343
♪ Hank is in The Garden now ♪

16:50.343 --> 16:54.560
♪ At home where he belongs ♪

16:54.560 --> 16:57.942
♪ ♪

16:57.942 --> 16:59.361
‐ Whoo!

16:59.361 --> 17:00.656
‐ Oh, it's beautiful, sweetie.

17:00.656 --> 17:03.662
That's great.
‐ Whoo!

17:03.662 --> 17:07.752
‐ Sarah, you want to share
your CO?

17:07.752 --> 17:09.172
‐ Uh, not right now.

17:09.172 --> 17:11.468
‐ Come on, Sarah.
It's your turn.

17:11.468 --> 17:13.515
‐ It's okay, Russel.
‐ No, no.

17:13.515 --> 17:16.980
There's an order to this.
‐ I said no.

17:16.980 --> 17:18.608
‐ Uh, I can go,

17:18.608 --> 17:20.529
if‐‐if that's okay
with everyone.

17:20.529 --> 17:21.823
‐ This should be good.

17:21.823 --> 17:23.577
‐ Yeah, no.
Of course.

17:23.577 --> 17:25.121
I mean, he was your father.

17:25.121 --> 17:27.917
You don't have to be a Meyerist
to share.

17:27.917 --> 17:31.216
‐ Thank you. I‐it means a lot
for me to be here.

17:31.216 --> 17:33.471
Well, uh,
a‐as most of you know,

17:33.471 --> 17:37.521
um, my father‐‐Dad and I
didn't speak for a long time.

17:37.521 --> 17:41.028
And, um, when he finally
reached out to me

17:41.028 --> 17:43.533
after all those years,
I was furious.

17:43.533 --> 17:47.082
But I was also so happy,
because faith or no faith,

17:47.082 --> 17:50.881
I still‐‐I loved Dad so much.

17:50.881 --> 17:52.635
So I‐I agreed to meet him,

17:52.635 --> 17:54.639
but only if
we did it at the racetrack.

17:54.639 --> 17:57.143
And, um, I never bet
on horses before,

17:57.143 --> 17:59.982
but I was just trying to punish
him by picking a place

17:59.982 --> 18:01.820
that I knew Meyerists
would hate.

18:01.820 --> 18:04.491
And the thing is, we ended up
having the best day.

18:04.491 --> 18:06.453
And then a few weeks later
when I asked him

18:06.453 --> 18:08.792
where he wanted to go,
he said the track.

18:08.792 --> 18:11.213
And month after month‐‐
‐ That's a great story, Tessa.

18:11.213 --> 18:13.885
Uh, who'd like to go next?
‐ She's not finished yet.

18:13.885 --> 18:15.889
‐ We're here to celebrate
Dad's life as a Meyerist,

18:15.889 --> 18:17.727
not talk about the times
he broke the rules.

18:17.727 --> 18:20.816
‐ Can we not argue right now?
‐ She's grieving.

18:20.816 --> 18:23.822
‐ Look, Hawk is right, okay?

18:23.822 --> 18:25.576
Tessa, please.

18:25.576 --> 18:28.038
‐ That's what
I was worried about.

18:28.038 --> 18:31.003
‐ Do you have something
you want to say, Nicole?

18:33.842 --> 18:35.596
‐ For someone
who didn't pick up her phone

18:35.596 --> 18:38.392
as her father was dying,
you have a lot of nerve‐‐

18:38.392 --> 18:42.066
- Okay, that is enough.
- Screw this.

18:42.066 --> 18:44.488
‐ Hawk, sweetie‐‐

18:47.118 --> 18:49.498
‐ Yeah, Sarah...

18:50.249 --> 18:52.086
Where were you?

18:52.086 --> 18:53.799
‐ It's none of your business
where she was, Russel.

18:53.799 --> 18:56.053
‐ Tessa, you can leave.
‐ Fuck you, Russel.

18:56.053 --> 18:58.224
He was her father.

18:58.224 --> 19:01.313
And I'm sorry if that
was inconvenient for you.

19:01.313 --> 19:05.488
I'm sorry that‐‐that Tessa
had the audacity

19:05.488 --> 19:07.283
to ask questions.

19:07.283 --> 19:09.204
You know, I know that
you just want to sit there

19:09.204 --> 19:11.124
and play your cute
little songs.

19:11.124 --> 19:13.045
But our perfectly
healthy father

19:13.045 --> 19:14.882
just died of a heart attack,

19:14.882 --> 19:17.596
and I'm sorry I don't have
a celebratory offering.

19:17.596 --> 19:20.769
I am pissed off.
‐ Then leave.

19:20.769 --> 19:22.731
‐ Gaby.
‐ No, these aren't cute songs

19:22.731 --> 19:26.363
and stories we tell
to make ourselves feel better.

19:26.363 --> 19:28.869
These are our sacred rites
and traditions.

19:28.869 --> 19:32.292
And I plan to honor
every one of them.

